<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1437,256,642]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis box="[151,270,256,281]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. A small 
<taxonomicName box="[387,553,256,282]" class="Chilopoda" family="Mecistocephalidae" genus="Arrup" kingdom="Animalia" order="Geophilomorpha" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[387,457,256,281]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Arrup</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
, with body length reaching at least 
<quantity box="[974,1036,256,282]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" unit="cm" value="1.0">1 cm</quantity>
. Frontal line absent. Distal article of the telopodite of the second maxillae without claw. Distal lobe of the medial projection of the first maxillae with parallel margins. A strong spiniform projection at the distal­external end of the basal article of second maxillae. Distal tooth of the forcipular article I relatively long and thin. Poison calyx reaching the distal part of the forcipular article I in females. Sternum of the last leg­bearing segment wider than long.
</paragraph>
